   <text:p text:style-name="P2"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2">partment of Labor , Bureau of Labor Statistics. Washington , D . C ., 1921.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2">* &quot; The immense credit resources of the federal reserve system were thus</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2">availed of by the Treasury during this period to make and maintain an</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P2">artificial money market .&quot;</text:p>
